# Time Complexity and Space Complexity:
- **Time Complexity :** ***O(n^4)**, where n is the length of s1. This is because there are n^2 possible starting indices for the substrings, and for each pair (i,j), we iterate over k, which can take up to l-1 values. Therefore, the innermost loop runs at most (l-1) times for each pair (i,j). The total number of iterations of the innermost loop is bounded by the sum of (l-1) over all possible values of l, which is O(n^3). The initialization of dp takes O(n^3) time, so the overall time complexity of the algorithm is O(n^4).*
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- **Space Complexity :** ***O(n^3)**, since we use a 3D array of size n+1 x n x n to store the intermediate results.*
