Hi LeetCode Heros, Hope you are doing great.
To solve this problem we just have to try all possible opration on first string and see If we can get the second string.
To do that we maintain two indcies one for the first string **l1** 
and the second for the second string **l2** 
and another variable for the current string size **len** 
lets start from this example input string 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/05d7ac32-b194-4fb0-93e3-3558db4ea0a1_1680149563.9615712.png)
lets declare that  
**a[l1: len]** -> substring of first string that start at index **l1** and has size = len
**b[l2: len]** -> substring of first string that start at index **l2** and has size = len
**solve(l1, l2, len)** = is **string a[l1:len] == b[l2:len]**
if **a[l1: len] == b[l2: len]** we are done just return true 
otherwise we can try all possoble split to split the first string 
try cut = 1 
we have string 
**a = x + y** 
**x = "4"**
**y = "132"**
we have 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/13147b93-ba46-4fc1-8d20-539faa98a030_1680149739.7371008.png)
and solve the two parts recursivley 
**solve(l1, l2, len) = solve(l1, l2, cut) && solve(l1+cut, l2+cut, (len-cut))**
or we make 
**a = y + x** 
**x = "4"**
**y = "132"**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/0d11bd7c-a4a7-4a9e-912a-9183f6f30eaa_1680150156.2705226.png)
keep in mind that string **b** still without change we just play with string **a**
and solve two parts recursivley 
**solve(l1, l2, len) = solve(l1, l2+(len-cut), cut) && solve(l1+cut, l2, len - cut)**
and these 3 variable are enough to determine the two substrings so we can memo on them

```
class Solution {
public:
    int dp[30][30][31];
    int solve(string& a, string& b, int l1, int l2, int len){
        int& ret = dp[l1][l2][len];
        if (~ret) return ret;
        ret = 0;
        bool sameString = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < len && sameString; i++){
            sameString &= (a[i+l1] == b[i+l2]);
        }
        ret = sameString;
		// if the two substrings are equal or only remain substring of size = 1 
        if (len == 1 || sameString) return sameString;
        for (int cut = 1; !ret && cut < len; cut++){
            ret = (solve(a, b, l1, l2, cut) && 
					solve(a, b, l1 + cut, l2 + cut, len - cut));
			// if ret == 1, we won't going to try this ... reason for ret || 
            ret = (ret || (solve(a, b, l1+cut, l2, len - cut) && 
							solve(a, b, l1, l2 + len - cut, cut)));
        }
        return ret;
    }
    bool isScramble(string s1, string s2) {
        memset(dp, -1 ,sizeof dp);
        return solve(s1, s2, 0, 0, s1.size());
    }
};
```

