# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
we will break our main string into all possible outcomes ==>>
i.e abc ==>> a bc or ab c
then we will try to swap positions of those parts and check all possible outcomes, hence we will use dp (memoizaiton) for that;

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
memoization

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int dp[30][30][30][30];
    bool helper(string one, string two, int i1, int j1, int i2, int j2){
        if(dp[i1][j1][i2][j2] != -1) return dp[i1][j1][i2][j2];
        bool counter = true;
        for(int i = i1, j = i2; i <= j1 && j <= j2; i++, j++){
            if(one[i] != two[j]) counter = false;
        }
        if(counter) return dp[i1][j1][i2][j2] = true;
        for(int i = i1; i < j1; i++){
            if(helper(one, two, i1, i, j2 - (i - i1), j2) && helper(one, two, i + 1, j1, i2, j2 - (i - i1) - 1)) return dp[i1][j1][i2][j2] = true;
            if(helper(one, two, i1, i, i2, i2 + (i - i1)) && helper(one, two, i + 1, j1, i2 + (i - i1) + 1, j2)) return dp[i1][j1][i2][j2] = true;
        }
        return dp[i1][j1][i2][j2] = false;
    }

    bool isScramble(string s1, string s2) {
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof(dp));
        return helper(s1, s2, 0, s1.size() - 1, 0, s2.size() - 1);
    }
};
```

