**idea**
1. use a vector : ```s1_v``` to record s1's char count from index ```0``` to ```i```.
2. use two vectors : 
2.a ```s2_front``` to record s2's char count from index ```0``` to ```i```.
2.b ```s2_back``` to record s2's char count from index ```length()-i``` to ```end```

```
if(s1_v == s2_front || s1_v == s2_back) : means scramble might exist when you cut at index-i

so let's divide into smaller problems :
if(s1_v == s2_front)
    isScramble(s1.front.substring,s2.front.substring) & isScramble(s1.back.substring,s2.back.substring)
else if(s1_v == s2_back)
    isScramble(s1.front.substring,s2.back.substring) & isScramble(s1.back.substring,s2.front.substring)
